Avalon Global Asset Management, LLC  Avalon Global  HomeStrategiesOur TeamContact    Founded in November 1999, Avalon Global Asset Management, LLC is a SEC registered investment advisor based in San Francisco investing across specific growth-oriented sectors in the developed world.  Asset Management, LLC  About UsInvestment ProcessContact      Copyright 2013. Avalon Global Asset Management, LLC. All rights reserved.  View on MobileAbout Us  Asset Management, LLC  Avalon Global  HomeStrategiesOur TeamContact    About UsInvestment ProcessContact  OverviewAvalon Global Asset Management, LLC (Avalon) aims to generate superior absolute and relative long-term returns employing an equity-based long/short strategy.Founding Partner and Portfolio Manager Nancy Kukacka and Avalon's team of investment professionals bring over 40 years of combined research and investment experience in global consumer, technology, media, healthcare, and business services industries.      Copyright 2013. Avalon Global Asset Management, LLC. All rights reserved.  View on MobileContact  Asset Management, LLC  Avalon Global  HomeStrategiesOur TeamContact  Avalon Global Asset Management, LLC100 Pine St.Suite 1900San Francisco, CA 94111Tel: 415.615.5200Fax: 415.615.5201​info@avalon-global.com      Copyright 2013. Avalon Global Asset Management, LLC. All rights reserved.  View on MobileStrategies  Asset Management, LLC  Avalon Global  HomeStrategiesOur TeamContact  StrategiesFor additional information on Avalon’s investment strategies, please contact info@avalon-global.com.      Copyright 2013. Avalon Global Asset Management, LLC. All rights reserved.  View on MobileInvestment Process  Asset Management, LLC  Avalon Global  HomeStrategiesOur TeamContact  About UsInvestment ProcessContact    Investment ProcessAvalon's investment philosophy is rooted in traditional "Growth Stock Theory" with disciplines that employ primary industry and company research as well as financial modeling. Avalon aims to identify dynamic managements and businesses with superior brand value and marketing prowess that are operating within industries underpinned by secular trends (fertile fields) for future growth. Our time horizon for investments are long, mirroring those of the most renowned companies who are committed to balancing current cash flow generation with capital investment for sustainable future growth.​Avalon's portfolio of long holdings is comprised of best-of-breed industry leaders, distinguished by established brand value, unique or disruptive product innovation, and differentiated marketing and distribution capabilities. In contrast, short positions center on businesses facing market share loss, product commoditization, or showing signs of under-investment and deteriorating profit quality.Across the five key sectors of focus (global consumer, technology, media, healthcare, business services industries), we construct a portfolio of core long stocks, tactically hedged with short stocks and options aimed to reduce market risk, cyclical industry and company-specific risk.      Copyright 2013. Avalon Global Asset Management, LLC. All rights reserved.  View on MobileOur Team  Asset Management, LLC  Avalon Global  HomeStrategiesOur TeamContact  Nancy KukackaJeffery ChristianRandi KittMatthew PendletonKathleen Ben    Photo: Neahga Leonard  Nancy Kukacka - Portfolio Manager, PrincipalPrior to forming Avalon Global, Ms. Kukacka was a Portfolio Manager at Montgomery Asset Management. She began her career there in 1995 as a Senior Analyst where she was responsible for global equity research in the consumer non-durables, consumer services and healthcare-related sectors, as well as managing a number of global equity portfolios and hedge funds. Prior to joining Montgomery, Ms. Kukacka worked at CS First Boston Investment (1994 to 1995), where she was an equity research analyst covering the consumer cyclical and non-durable sectors. Before that, she was an Equity Research Analyst at Dresdner RCM Capital Management (1990 to 1994), providing fundamental-based analysis for more than $12 billion in equity investments. Ms. Kukacka holds a Bachelor of Arts degree in Economics with minors in Chemistry and Biology from Bucknell University.      Copyright 2013. Avalon Global Asset Management, LLC. All rights reserved.  View on MobileInvestment Process  Asset Management, LLC  Avalon Global  HomeStrategiesOur TeamContact  About UsInvestment ProcessContact    Investment ProcessAvalon's investment philosophy is rooted in traditional "Growth Stock Theory" with disciplines that employ primary industry and company research as well as financial modeling. Avalon aims to identify dynamic managements and businesses with superior brand value and marketing prowess that are operating within industries underpinned by secular trends (fertile fields) for future growth. Our time horizon for investments are long, mirroring those of the most renowned companies who are committed to balancing current cash flow generation with capital investment for sustainable future growth.​Avalon's portfolio of long holdings is comprised of best-of-breed industry leaders, distinguished by established brand value, unique or disruptive product innovation, and differentiated marketing and distribution capabilities. In contrast, short positions center on businesses facing market share loss, product commoditization, or showing signs of under-investment and deteriorating profit quality.Across the five key sectors of focus (global consumer, technology, media, healthcare, business services industries), we construct a portfolio of core long stocks, tactically hedged with short stocks and options aimed to reduce market risk, cyclical industry and company-specific risk.      Copyright 2013. Avalon Global Asset Management, LLC. All rights reserved.  View on Mobile



